   global trend (Yokoyama, S., Strategy of alliance and confederacy,
   Toyokeizai shinpou, 1998 (Japanese)). Mass media is busy reporting M\&A
   (both cross-border and cross-industry), which were unimaginable
   combinations before. Integration of enterprise information processing
   systems, however, always remains a problem, even in this seemingly
   routine M\&A age, presenting difficulties to merged companies long after
   the merger (Mitsubishi Research Institute, in: Proceedings of the
   Innovation of Group Management and Measures of Computerization, 1999
