Abstract = {{Today many industrial enterprises have to meet several challenges like
   individual customer production, enterprise resource planning, electronic
   market places, B2C and B2B communication as well as E-commerce
   applications. In this context supporting information systems are
   required, which allow the integration of heterogeneous software systems
   and the corresponding data sources in order to optimize both
   collaboration of in-house software components and data communication
   with other business partners. For industrial enterprises efficient
   management of product data is of major importance because it
   significantly increases the productivity of engineers and organizations
   that deal with information involved in the process of designing,
   manufacturing and maintaining a product. Electronic data interchange
   (EDI) is the most important prerequisite for electronic collaboration
