Abstract = {{Complementary Processes (CP) are used to form Complementary
   Collaborative Processes. The collaborative processes perform individual
   functions of the Information System (IS). A group of collaborative
   processes can be referred to as a Complementary Production Lines (CPL).
   Each of the processes of a CPL is performing it's task concurrently and
   In-Concert with its associated tasks or Side-by-Side. When associated
   tasks are performing Side-by-Side and In-Concert, it is synonymous with
   parallel processing. CPL's are used as a method to expand the
   computation resources of Processors. These methods are not available in
   current resources. This will allow the scalability of software (SW)
   resources to grow linearly and/or from 1 Processor to ``N{''}
   Processors. This is a method of obtaining parallel processing from
   Serial Processes. When Collaborative Processes of one Processor are
   performing Side-by-Side, with other similar Processors, this action is
   synonymous with parallel Processors and/or Replication of SW Processors.
   Replication or duplication of Processors is a method for linear
   expandability, Fault Tolerance, and Availability that approaches 100\%.
   This will allow the enterprises to have an integrated IS System that
   begins with it's primary Users (Hand Held Devices or Thin Clients),
   progress through intermediate layers of Processors, and terminate in a
